The African National Congress held a special NEC meeting amid the mayhem, which started as a pro-Zuma protest. JOHANNESBURG - The ANC is condemning the continuing looting and damage of property in KwaZulu Natal and Gauteng. ANC Deputy Secretary-General Jessie Duarte says the protests and looting will have a devastating effect on South Africa's economy. READ: Violence in SA: More police officers called in Duarte says the poor and marginalised will bear the brunt.